18 (i) The minimum school term under section 163.021;
19 (ii) Dyslexia assessment and parent notification under section 167.645;
20 (iii) Student participation in moderate physical activity under section 167.720;
21 (iv) Interscholastic youth sports brain injury prevention under section 167.765;
22 (v) Conducting educational programs and activities and observing Veterans Day
23 under section 170.049;
24 (vi) Providing cardiopulmonary resuscitation instruction and training in high
25 school under section 170.310;
26 (vii) Displaying the flag of the United States of America and participating in the
27 recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance to the flag of the United States of America under
28 section 171.021;
29 (viii) Providing access to official recruiting representatives of the military under
30 section 171.026;
31 (ix) Setting an opening school term date that is no earlier than fourteen days
32 prior to the first Monday in September under section 171.031; and
33 (x) Prevailing wage requirements for school construction projects under section
34 290.230; and
35 (b) Any of the following entities that [is] are incorporated in Missouri [and]; that
36 [does] do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, or national origin; and that comply
37 with the laws and regulations regarding the requirements listed in subparagraph b. of
38 paragraph (a) of this subdivision shall be deemed a qualified school:
39 [(a)] a. A charter school as defined in section 160.400;
40 [(b)] b. A private school;
41 [(c)] c. A public school as defined in section 160.011; or
42 [(d)] d. A public or private virtual school;
43 (9) "Qualified student", any elementary or secondary school student who is a resident
44 of this state, who is not an illegal alien, and who:
45 (a) Has an approved "individualized education [plan] program" (IEP) developed
46 under the federal Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA), 20 U.S.C. Section 1400
47 et seq., as amended; or
48 (b) Is a member of a household whose total annual income does not exceed an amount
49 equal to three hundred percent of the income standard used to qualify for free and reduced
50 price lunches, and that meets at least one of the following qualifications:
51 a. Attended a public school as a full-time student for at least one semester during the
52 previous twelve months;
53 b. Is a child who is eligible to begin kindergarten or first grade under sections 160.051
54 to 160.055; or

